'''细胞增殖'''是指细胞生长和分裂成两个子细胞的过程<ref name="ConlonRaff1999">{{Cite journal|title=Size Control in Animal Development|last=Conlon|first=Ian|last2=Raff|first2=Martin|journal=Cell|issue=2|doi=10.1016/S0092-8674(00)80563-2|year=1999|volume=96|pages=235–244|issn=00928674|pmid=9988218}}</ref><ref name="GrewalEdgar2003">{{Cite journal|title=Controlling cell division in yeast and animals: does size matter?|last=Grewal|first=Savraj S|last2=Edgar|first2=Bruce A|journal=Journal of Biology|issue=1|doi=10.1186/1475-4924-2-5|year=2003|volume=2|pages=5|issn=14754924|pmid=12733996|subscription=free}}</ref><ref name="Neufeldde la Cruz1998">{{Cite journal|title=Coordination of Growth and Cell Division in the Drosophila Wing|last=Neufeld|first=Thomas P|last2=de la Cruz|first2=Aida Flor A|journal=Cell|issue=7|doi=10.1016/S0092-8674(00)81462-2|year=1998|volume=93|pages=1183–1193|issn=00928674|pmid=9657151|last3=Johnston|first3=Laura A|last4=Edgar|first4=Bruce A}}</ref><ref name="Thompson">{{Cite journal|title=Developmental control of cell growth and division in Drosophila|last=Thompson|first=Barry J.|journal=Current Opinion in Cell Biology|issue=6|doi=10.1016/j.ceb.2010.08.018|year=2010|volume=22|pages=788–794|pmid=20833011}}</ref>。细胞增殖使细胞数量成倍增加，因此它是[[组织_(生物学)|组织]]生长的快速机制。细胞增殖要求细胞生长和[[细胞分裂|细胞分裂]]同时发生，以使细胞的平均大小保持不变。细胞增殖与细胞生长或细胞分裂不同的是，细胞分裂時可以不发生细胞生长，這樣會生成许多小細胞(如[[卵裂|卵裂]])，而细胞生长可以不发生细胞分裂，因而會产生单个较大的细胞(如[[神經元|神經元]]的生长)<ref name="Saucedo2002">{{Cite journal|title=Why size matters: altering cell size|last=Saucedo|first=L|journal=Current Opinion in Genetics & Development|issue=5|doi=10.1016/S0959-437X(02)00341-6|year=2002|volume=12|pages=565–571|issn=0959437X|pmid=12200162}}</ref>。细胞总数由细胞增殖率减去[[细胞死亡|细胞死亡率]]所决定。

